    "Comprising over 50,000 instances, it is notable for its linguistic complexity, including greater lexical diversity, syntactic variation, and discourse phenomena compared to earlier datasets.",
    "Evaluation is primarily based on five metrics: BLEU, NIST, ME-TEOR, ROUGE-L, and CIDEr.",
    "BLEU measures n-gram overlap between the generated text and human references, emphasizing precision.",
    "METEOR accounts for synonymy and stemming, providing a more nuanced assessment of similarity.",
    "ROUGE-L evaluates fluency and structure through the longest common subsequence."
